name: AR Treasurer
tweet: I was privileged to be among so many Vietnam War veterans today during a ceremony held in their honor on the Capitol grounds. I was particularly moved by Sen. Dave Wallace's speech discussing the fear with which these veterans lived each day and which still remains in them today.  https://t.co/v0NT0g72R4

name: AR Treasurer
tweet: 1/2: This week's Veteran feature is Lt. Col. David Arnold Harrington of Maumelle, who served in the U.S. Navy & later the U.S. Army during Vietnam, where he earned 2 Bronze Star Medals, the Meritorious Service Medal, 9 awards of the Air Medal, and 2 Army Commendation Medals.  https://t.co/j0oAjQ36nQ

name: AR Treasurer
tweet: 2/2: After retirement, he was appointed by Presidents Ronald Reagan, George H.W. Bush and Bill Clinton to the Intergovernmental Policy Advisor Committee to the U.S. Trade Commission, and to the Industry Advisory Committee to the U.S. Secretary of Commerce.  https://t.co/xvveZzPAtp

name: AR Treasurer
tweet: Today is National Medal of Honor Day, a day to recognize those servicemen/women who have received the nation's highest military honor for valor in combat. The Medal of Honor was first awarded on this day in 1863. There are over 3,500 members who have since received this award.  https://t.co/jtQSkg5e9g

name: AR Treasurer
tweet: Arkansas is home to nearly 30 Medal of Honor recipients whose names are listed on the Arkansas Military Veterans' Hall of Fame display located inside our office in the State Capitol.   #MedalofHonor #Veterans #CongressionalMedalofHonor  https://t.co/CSC06F8aWZ

name: AR Treasurer
tweet: As I look back on my tenure as Treasurer, one of the highlights has been working with the legislature to make this office run more efficiently. Act 133 of 2019 is just one example of how I've been able to accomplish that. #efficiency  https://t.co/VhRNzzQCYq
